SECTIONS
This file defines all sections, their ordering, impact levels, and descriptions. The section ID (in parentheses) IT filename prefix used to group rules. 
--- 
1. COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE (ARCHITECTURE)
Impact: HIGH Description: Fundamental patterns for structuring components to avoid prop proliferation and enable flexible composition. 
2. STATE MANAGEMENT (STATE)
Impact: MEDIUM Description: Patterns for lifting state and managing shared context across composed components. 
3. IMPLEMENTATION PATTERNS (PATTERNS)
Impact: MEDIUM Description: Specific techniques for implementing compound components and context providers. 
4. REACT 19 APIS (REACT19)
Impact: MEDIUM Description: React 19+ only. Don't use forwardRef; UU() IO useContext(). 